    "targetColor": "blue",
    "summary": "Reiterated blocking issue: missing focus management JS",
    "content": "Already sent my full HTMX review of Step 10. To reiterate the key point:\n\n**BLOCKING: Missing focus management JS.** There is no `static/js/someday-maybe-focus.js` file and no `{% block scripts %}` in `someday_maybe.html`. When items are deleted or activated via HTMX, focus is lost to `<body>`, violating WCAG 2.4.3. The empty state toggle also won't work. Every other list feature has this JS file.\n\nFix: Create `static/js/someday-maybe-focus.js` (adapt from `waiting-for-focus.js` with class names changed to `someday-maybe-item` etc.) and add `{% block scripts %}<script src=\"/static/js/someday-maybe-focus.js\"></script>{% endblock %}` to the template.\n\nEverything else is approved. See my earlier message for the full detailed review.\n"
  }
}
